{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":476,"text":"I do two things:"},{"time":1651,"text":"I design mobile computers\nand I study brains."},{"time":3793,"text":"Today's talk is about brains\nand -- (Audience member cheers)"},{"time":6747,"text":"Yay! I have a brain fan out there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":8588,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":11759,"text":"If I could have my first slide,"},{"time":13338,"text":"you'll see the title of my talk\nand my two affiliations."},{"time":16211,"text":"So what I'm going to talk about is why\nwe don't have a good brain theory,"},{"time":19703,"text":"why it is important\nthat we should develop one"},{"time":22004,"text":"and what we can do about it."},{"time":23511,"text":"I'll try to do all that in 20 minutes."},{"time":25359,"text":"I have two affiliations."},{"time":26534,"text":"Most of you know me\nfrom my Palm and Handspring days,"},{"time":29090,"text":"but I also run a nonprofit\nscientific research institute"},{"time":31797,"text":"called the Redwood Neuroscience\nInstitute in Menlo Park."},{"time":34453,"text":"We study theoretical neuroscience\nand how the neocortex works."},{"time":37865,"text":"I'm going to talk all about that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39487,"text":"I have one slide on my other life,\nthe computer life,"},{"time":42256,"text":"and that's this slide here."},{"time":43581,"text":"These are some of the products\nI've worked on over the last 20 years,"},{"time":46873,"text":"starting from the very original laptop"},{"time":48739,"text":"to some of the first tablet computers"},{"time":50550,"text":"and so on, ending up\nmost recently with the Treo,"},{"time":52872,"text":"and we're continuing to do this."},{"time":54428,"text":"I've done this because\nI believe mobile computing"},{"time":56753,"text":"is the future of personal computing,"},{"time":58501,"text":"and I'm trying to make\nthe world a little bit better"},{"time":60979,"text":"by working on these things."},{"time":62299,"text":"But this was, I admit, all an accident."},{"time":64197,"text":"I really didn't want to do\nany of these products."},{"time":66529,"text":"Very early in my career"},{"time":67935,"text":"I decided I was not going to be\nin the computer industry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70649,"text":"Before that, I just have to tell you"},{"time":72394,"text":"about this picture of Graffiti\nI picked off the web the other day."},{"time":75526,"text":"I was looking for a picture for Graffiti\nthat'll text input language."},{"time":78803,"text":"I found a website dedicated to teachers\nwho want to make script-writing things"},{"time":82516,"text":"across the top of their blackboard,"},{"time":84214,"text":"and they had added Graffiti to it,\nand I'm sorry about that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87071,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":89342,"text":"So what happened was,"},{"time":90666,"text":"when I was young and got out\nof engineering school at Cornell in '79,"},{"time":95589,"text":"I went to work for Intel\nand was in the computer industry,"},{"time":98800,"text":"and three months into that,\nI fell in love with something else."},{"time":102226,"text":"I said, \"I made\nthe wrong career choice here,\""},{"time":105294,"text":"and I fell in love with brains."},{"time":107557,"text":"This is not a real brain."},{"time":109114,"text":"This is a picture of one, a line drawing."},{"time":111857,"text":"And I don't remember\nexactly how it happened,"},{"time":114000,"text":"but I have one recollection,\nwhich was pretty strong in my mind."},{"time":117539,"text":"In September of 1979,"},{"time":119173,"text":"Scientific American came out\nwith a single-topic issue about the brain."},{"time":122561,"text":"It was one of their best issues ever."},{"time":124523,"text":"They talked about the neuron,\ndevelopment, disease, vision"},{"time":127494,"text":"and all the things you might want\nto know about brains."},{"time":130114,"text":"It was really quite impressive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131640,"text":"One might've had the impression\nwe knew a lot about brains."},{"time":134436,"text":"But the last article in that issue\nwas written by Francis Crick of DNA fame."},{"time":138655,"text":"Today is, I think, the 50th anniversary\nof the discovery of DNA."},{"time":141703,"text":"And he wrote a story basically saying,\nthis is all well and good,"},{"time":144802,"text":"but you know, we don't know\ndiddly squat about brains,"},{"time":147569,"text":"and no one has a clue how they work,"},{"time":149332,"text":"so don't believe what anyone tells you."},{"time":151222,"text":"This is a quote\nfrom that article, he says:"},{"time":153411,"text":"\"What is conspicuously lacking\" --\nhe's a very proper British gentleman --"},{"time":157728,"text":"\"What is conspicuously lacking\nis a broad framework of ideas"},{"time":160582,"text":"in which to interpret\nthese different approaches.\""},{"time":162958,"text":"I thought the word \"framework\" was great."},{"time":164950,"text":"He didn't say we didn't have a theory."},{"time":166791,"text":"He says we don't even know\nhow to begin to think about it."},{"time":169540,"text":"We don't even have a framework."},{"time":171056,"text":"We are in the pre-paradigm days,\nif you want to use Thomas Kuhn."},{"time":174130,"text":"So I fell in love with this."},{"time":175493,"text":"I said, look: We have all this knowledge\nabout brains -- how hard can it be?"},{"time":179092,"text":"It's something we can work on\nin my lifetime; I could make a difference."},{"time":182554,"text":"So I tried to get out of the computer\nbusiness, into the brain business."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186197,"text":"First, I went to MIT,\nthe AI lab was there."},{"time":188225,"text":"I said, I want to build\nintelligent machines too,"},{"time":190644,"text":"but I want to study how brains work first."},{"time":193185,"text":"And they said, \"Oh, you\ndon't need to do that."},{"time":195515,"text":"You're just going to program\ncomputers, that's all."},{"time":197929,"text":"I said, you really ought to study brains."},{"time":199916,"text":"They said, \"No, you're wrong.\""},{"time":201372,"text":"I said, \"No, you're wrong,\"\nand I didn't get in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203642,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":204744,"text":"I was a little disappointed --\npretty young --"},{"time":206923,"text":"but I went back again a few years later,"},{"time":208883,"text":"this time in California,\nand I went to Berkeley."},{"time":211266,"text":"And I said, I'll go\nin from the biological side."},{"time":213720,"text":"So I got in the PhD program in biophysics."},{"time":216833,"text":"I was like, I'm studying brains now.\nWell, I want to study theory."},{"time":220267,"text":"They said, \"You can't\nstudy theory about brains."},{"time":222560,"text":"You can't get funded for that."},{"time":224579,"text":"And as a graduate student,\nyou can't do that.\""},{"time":226758,"text":"So I said, oh my gosh."},{"time":228000,"text":"I was depressed; I said, but I can\nmake a difference in this field."},{"time":231179,"text":"I went back in the computer industry"},{"time":233211,"text":"and said, I'll have to work\nhere for a while."},{"time":235340,"text":"That's when I designed\nall those computer products."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237757,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":239082,"text":"I said, I want to do this\nfor four years, make some money,"},{"time":242000,"text":"I was having a family,\nand I would mature a bit,"},{"time":246000,"text":"and maybe the business\nof neuroscience would mature a bit."},{"time":248840,"text":"Well, it took longer than four years.\nIt's been about 16 years."},{"time":251865,"text":"But I'm doing it now,\nand I'm going to tell you about it."},{"time":254605,"text":"So why should we have a good brain theory?"},{"time":256915,"text":"Well, there's lots of reasons\npeople do science."},{"time":260041,"text":"The most basic one is,\npeople like to know things."},{"time":262982,"text":"We're curious, and we go out\nand get knowledge."},{"time":265201,"text":"Why do we study ants? It's interesting."},{"time":267091,"text":"Maybe we'll learn something useful,\nbut it's interesting and fascinating."},{"time":270581,"text":"But sometimes a science\nhas other attributes"},{"time":272662,"text":"which makes it really interesting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274515,"text":"Sometimes a science will tell\nsomething about ourselves;"},{"time":277166,"text":"it'll tell us who we are."},{"time":278414,"text":"Evolution did this\nand Copernicus did this,"},{"time":281190,"text":"where we have a new\nunderstanding of who we are."},{"time":283548,"text":"And after all, we are our brains.\nMy brain is talking to your brain."},{"time":287000,"text":"Our bodies are hanging along for the ride,"},{"time":289054,"text":"but my brain is talking to your brain."},{"time":290903,"text":"And if we want to understand\nwho we are and how we feel and perceive,"},{"time":294175,"text":"we need to understand brains."},{"time":295590,"text":"Another thing is sometimes science leads\nto big societal benefits, technologies,"},{"time":299398,"text":"or businesses or whatever."},{"time":300713,"text":"This is one, too, because\nwhen we understand how brains work,"},{"time":303615,"text":"we'll be able to build\nintelligent machines."},{"time":305703,"text":"That's a good thing on the whole,"},{"time":307425,"text":"with tremendous benefits to society,"},{"time":309307,"text":"just like a fundamental technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311000,"text":"So why don't we have\na good theory of brains?"},{"time":313874,"text":"People have been working\non it for 100 years."},{"time":316066,"text":"Let's first take a look\nat what normal science looks like."},{"time":318809,"text":"This is normal science."},{"time":320020,"text":"Normal science is a nice balance\nbetween theory and experimentalists."},{"time":324118,"text":"The theorist guy says,\n\"I think this is what's going on,\""},{"time":326833,"text":"the experimentalist says, \"You're wrong.\""},{"time":328818,"text":"It goes back and forth,\nthis works in physics, this in geology."},{"time":331846,"text":"But if this is normal science,\nwhat does neuroscience look like?"},{"time":334879,"text":"This is what neuroscience looks like."},{"time":336698,"text":"We have this mountain of data,"},{"time":338164,"text":"which is anatomy, physiology and behavior."},{"time":340258,"text":"You can't imagine how much detail\nwe know about brains."},{"time":343476,"text":"There were 28,000 people who went\nto the neuroscience conference this year,"},{"time":347092,"text":"and every one of them\nis doing research in brains."},{"time":349479,"text":"A lot of data, but no theory."},{"time":351197,"text":"There's a little wimpy box on top there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353221,"text":"And theory has not played a role\nin any sort of grand way"},{"time":356627,"text":"in the neurosciences."},{"time":358080,"text":"And it's a real shame."},{"time":359344,"text":"Now, why has this come about?"},{"time":360759,"text":"If you ask neuroscientists\nwhy is this the state of affairs,"},{"time":363771,"text":"first, they'll admit it."},{"time":365041,"text":"But if you ask them, they say,"},{"time":366550,"text":"there's various reasons\nwe don't have a good brain theory."},{"time":369306,"text":"Some say we still don't have enough data,"},{"time":371299,"text":"we need more information,\nthere's all these things we don't know."},{"time":374382,"text":"Well, I just told you there's data\ncoming out of your ears."},{"time":377247,"text":"We have so much information,\nwe don't even know how to organize it."},{"time":380435,"text":"What good is more going to do?"},{"time":381897,"text":"Maybe we'll be lucky and discover\nsome magic thing, but I don't think so."},{"time":385369,"text":"This is a symptom of the fact\nthat we just don't have a theory."},{"time":388366,"text":"We don't need more data,\nwe need a good theory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391000,"text":"Another one is sometimes people say,"},{"time":392822,"text":"\"Brains are so complex,\nit'll take another 50 years.\""},{"time":396000,"text":"I even think Chris said something\nlike this yesterday, something like,"},{"time":399378,"text":"it's one of the most complicated\nthings in the universe."},{"time":402029,"text":"That's not true -- you're more\ncomplicated than your brain."},{"time":404843,"text":"You've got a brain."},{"time":406018,"text":"And although the brain\nlooks very complicated,"},{"time":408192,"text":"things look complicated\nuntil you understand them."},{"time":410552,"text":"That's always been the case."},{"time":411911,"text":"So we can say, my neocortex,\nthe part of the brain I'm interested in,"},{"time":415178,"text":"has 30 billion cells."},{"time":416354,"text":"But, you know what?\nIt's very, very regular."},{"time":418810,"text":"In fact, it looks like it's the same thing\nrepeated over and over again."},{"time":422228,"text":"It's not as complex as it looks.\nThat's not the issue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424788,"text":"Some people say,\nbrains can't understand brains."},{"time":427099,"text":"Very Zen-like. Woo."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429111,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":431323,"text":"You know, it sounds good, but why?\nI mean, what's the point?"},{"time":434206,"text":"It's just a bunch of cells.\nYou understand your liver."},{"time":436799,"text":"It's got a lot of cells in it too, right?"},{"time":438800,"text":"So, you know, I don't think\nthere's anything to that."},{"time":441318,"text":"And finally, some people say,"},{"time":443454,"text":"\"I don't feel like a bunch\nof cells -- I'm conscious."},{"time":446461,"text":"I've got this experience,\nI'm in the world."},{"time":448554,"text":"I can't be just a bunch of cells.\""},{"time":450488,"text":"Well, people used to believe\nthere was a life force to be living,"},{"time":453735,"text":"and we now know\nthat's really not true at all."},{"time":456168,"text":"And there's really no evidence,"},{"time":458090,"text":"other than that people just disbelieve\nthat cells can do what they do."},{"time":461488,"text":"So some people have fallen\ninto the pit of metaphysical dualism,"},{"time":464553,"text":"some really smart people, too,\nbut we can reject all that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467307,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":470226,"text":"No, there's something else,"},{"time":471991,"text":"something really fundamental, and it is:"},{"time":474000,"text":"another reason why we don't have\na good brain theory"},{"time":476475,"text":"is because we have an intuitive,\nstrongly held but incorrect assumption"},{"time":482034,"text":"that has prevented us\nfrom seeing the answer."},{"time":484170,"text":"There's something we believe that just,\nit's obvious, but it's wrong."},{"time":487982,"text":"Now, there's a history of this in science\nand before I tell you what it is,"},{"time":491572,"text":"I'll tell you about the history\nof it in science."},{"time":493895,"text":"Look at other scientific revolutions --"},{"time":495829,"text":"the solar system, that's Copernicus,"},{"time":497732,"text":"Darwin's evolution,\nand tectonic plates, that's Wegener."},{"time":501059,"text":"They all have a lot in common\nwith brain science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":503378,"text":"First, they had a lot\nof unexplained data. A lot of it."},{"time":506068,"text":"But it got more manageable\nonce they had a theory."},{"time":508886,"text":"The best minds were stumped --\nreally smart people."},{"time":511717,"text":"We're not smarter now than they were then;"},{"time":513745,"text":"it just turns out it's really\nhard to think of things,"},{"time":516296,"text":"but once you've thought of them,\nit's easy to understand."},{"time":518996,"text":"My daughters understood\nthese three theories,"},{"time":521126,"text":"in their basic framework, in kindergarten."},{"time":523668,"text":"It's not that hard --\nhere's the apple, here's the orange,"},{"time":526958,"text":"the Earth goes around, that kind of stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":529000,"text":"Another thing is the answer\nwas there all along,"},{"time":531610,"text":"but we kind of ignored it\nbecause of this obvious thing."},{"time":534413,"text":"It was an intuitive,\nstrongly held belief that was wrong."},{"time":537287,"text":"In the case of the solar system,"},{"time":539001,"text":"the idea that the Earth is spinning,"},{"time":540785,"text":"the surface is going\na thousand miles an hour,"},{"time":543000,"text":"and it's going through the solar system\nat a million miles an hour --"},{"time":546273,"text":"this is lunacy; we all know\nthe Earth isn't moving."},{"time":548773,"text":"Do you feel like you're moving\na thousand miles an hour?"},{"time":551674,"text":"If you said Earth was spinning\naround in space and was huge --"},{"time":554617,"text":"they would lock you up,\nthat's what they did back then."},{"time":557232,"text":"So it was intuitive and obvious.\nNow, what about evolution?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":560531,"text":"Evolution, same thing."},{"time":561709,"text":"We taught our kids the Bible says\nGod created all these species,"},{"time":564813,"text":"cats are cats; dogs are dogs;\npeople are people; plants are plants;"},{"time":567980,"text":"they don't change."},{"time":569245,"text":"Noah put them on the ark\nin that order, blah, blah."},{"time":571918,"text":"The fact is, if you believe in evolution,\nwe all have a common ancestor."},{"time":575337,"text":"We all have a common ancestor\nwith the plant in the lobby!"},{"time":578643,"text":"This is what evolution tells us.\nAnd it's true. It's kind of unbelievable."},{"time":582353,"text":"And the same thing about tectonic plates."},{"time":584934,"text":"All the mountains and the continents"},{"time":586680,"text":"are kind of floating around\non top of the Earth."},{"time":589048,"text":"It doesn't make any sense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590318,"text":"So what is the intuitive,\nbut incorrect assumption,"},{"time":594943,"text":"that's kept us from understanding brains?"},{"time":596934,"text":"I'll tell you. It'll seem obvious\nthat it's correct. That's the point."},{"time":600251,"text":"Then I'll make an argument why\nyou're incorrect on the other assumption."},{"time":603709,"text":"The intuitive but obvious thing is:"},{"time":605415,"text":"somehow, intelligence\nis defined by behavior;"},{"time":607753,"text":"we're intelligent\nbecause of how we do things"},{"time":610127,"text":"and how we behave intelligently."},{"time":611723,"text":"And I'm going to tell you that's wrong."},{"time":613626,"text":"Intelligence is defined by prediction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":615781,"text":"I'm going to work you\nthrough this in a few slides,"},{"time":618220,"text":"and give you an example\nof what this means."},{"time":620338,"text":"Here's a system."},{"time":621663,"text":"Engineers and scientists\nlike to look at systems like this."},{"time":624595,"text":"They say, we have a thing in a box.\nWe have its inputs and outputs."},{"time":627782,"text":"The AI people said, the thing in the box\nis a programmable computer,"},{"time":631046,"text":"because it's equivalent to a brain."},{"time":632749,"text":"We'll feed it some inputs and get it\nto do something, have some behavior."},{"time":636279,"text":"Alan Turing defined the Turing test,\nwhich essentially says,"},{"time":639125,"text":"we'll know if something's intelligent\nif it behaves identical to a human --"},{"time":642702,"text":"a behavioral metric\nof what intelligence is"},{"time":644832,"text":"that has stuck in our minds\nfor a long time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647000,"text":"Reality, though --\nI call it real intelligence."},{"time":649416,"text":"Real intelligence\nis built on something else."},{"time":651615,"text":"We experience the world\nthrough a sequence of patterns,"},{"time":654853,"text":"and we store them, and we recall them."},{"time":657026,"text":"When we recall them,\nwe match them up against reality,"},{"time":659595,"text":"and we're making predictions all the time."},{"time":661870,"text":"It's an internal metric;\nthere's an internal metric about us,"},{"time":664852,"text":"saying, do we understand the world,\nam I making predictions, and so on."},{"time":668218,"text":"You're all being intelligent now,\nbut you're not doing anything."},{"time":671244,"text":"Maybe you're scratching yourself,\nbut you're not doing anything."},{"time":674270,"text":"But you're being intelligent;\nyou're understanding what I'm saying."},{"time":677450,"text":"Because you're intelligent\nand you speak English,"},{"time":679769,"text":"you know the word at the end of this"},{"time":681544,"text":"sentence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":682727,"text":"The word came to you;\nyou make these predictions all the time."},{"time":685903,"text":"What I'm saying is,"},{"time":687626,"text":"the internal prediction\nis the output in the neocortex,"},{"time":690281,"text":"and somehow, prediction\nleads to intelligent behavior."},{"time":692846,"text":"Here's how that happens:"},{"time":694021,"text":"Let's start with a non-intelligent brain."},{"time":696000,"text":"I'll argue a non-intelligent brain,\nwe'll call it an old brain."},{"time":699033,"text":"And we'll say it's\na non-mammal, like a reptile,"},{"time":701928,"text":"say, an alligator; we have an alligator."},{"time":703937,"text":"And the alligator has\nsome very sophisticated senses."},{"time":707332,"text":"It's got good eyes and ears\nand touch senses and so on,"},{"time":710562,"text":"a mouth and a nose."},{"time":712055,"text":"It has very complex behavior."},{"time":714070,"text":"It can run and hide. It has fears\nand emotions. It can eat you."},{"time":718000,"text":"It can attack.\nIt can do all kinds of stuff."},{"time":722193,"text":"But we don't consider\nthe alligator very intelligent,"},{"time":725073,"text":"not in a human sort of way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726773,"text":"But it has all this complex\nbehavior already."},{"time":729510,"text":"Now in evolution, what happened?"},{"time":731335,"text":"First thing that happened\nin evolution with mammals"},{"time":733744,"text":"is we started to develop a thing\ncalled the neocortex."},{"time":736299,"text":"I'm going to represent the neocortex\nby this box on top of the old brain."},{"time":740116,"text":"Neocortex means \"new layer.\"\nIt's a new layer on top of your brain."},{"time":743493,"text":"It's the wrinkly thing\non the top of your head"},{"time":745860,"text":"that got wrinkly because it got shoved\nin there and doesn't fit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":748968,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":750000,"text":"Literally, it's about the size\nof a table napkin"},{"time":752266,"text":"and doesn't fit, so it's wrinkly."},{"time":753864,"text":"Now, look at how I've drawn this."},{"time":755633,"text":"The old brain is still there."},{"time":757043,"text":"You still have that alligator brain.\nYou do. It's your emotional brain."},{"time":760722,"text":"It's all those gut reactions you have."},{"time":763476,"text":"On top of it, we have this memory system\ncalled the neocortex."},{"time":766770,"text":"And the memory system is sitting\nover the sensory part of the brain."},{"time":771088,"text":"So as the sensory input\ncomes in and feeds from the old brain,"},{"time":774167,"text":"it also goes up into the neocortex."},{"time":776345,"text":"And the neocortex is just memorizing."},{"time":778282,"text":"It's sitting there saying, I'm going\nto memorize all the things going on:"},{"time":781867,"text":"where I've been, people I've seen,\nthings I've heard, and so on."},{"time":784910,"text":"And in the future, when it sees\nsomething similar to that again,"},{"time":788296,"text":"in a similar environment,\nor the exact same environment,"},{"time":790955,"text":"it'll start playing it back:\n\"Oh, I've been here before,\""},{"time":794534,"text":"and when you were here before,\nthis happened next."},{"time":796922,"text":"It allows you to predict the future."},{"time":798672,"text":"It literally feeds back\nthe signals into your brain;"},{"time":802092,"text":"they'll let you see\nwhat's going to happen next,"},{"time":804381,"text":"will let you hear the word\n\"sentence\" before I said it."},{"time":807000,"text":"And it's this feeding\nback into the old brain"},{"time":810209,"text":"that will allow you to make\nmore intelligent decisions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":812810,"text":"This is the most important slide\nof my talk, so I'll dwell on it a little."},{"time":816323,"text":"And all the time you say,\n\"Oh, I can predict things,\""},{"time":819922,"text":"so if you're a rat and you go\nthrough a maze, and you learn the maze,"},{"time":823306,"text":"next time you're in one,\nyou have the same behavior."},{"time":825769,"text":"But suddenly, you're smarter;\nyou say, \"I recognize this maze,"},{"time":828784,"text":"I know which way to go; I've been here\nbefore; I can envision the future.\""},{"time":832350,"text":"That's what it's doing."},{"time":833542,"text":"This is true for all mammals --"},{"time":836406,"text":"in humans, it got a lot worse."},{"time":838461,"text":"Humans actually developed\nthe front of the neocortex,"},{"time":841072,"text":"called the anterior part of the neocortex."},{"time":843317,"text":"And nature did a little trick."},{"time":844779,"text":"It copied the posterior,\nthe back part, which is sensory,"},{"time":847490,"text":"and put it in the front."},{"time":848665,"text":"Humans uniquely have\nthe same mechanism on the front,"},{"time":851169,"text":"but we use it for motor control."}]},{"cues":[{"time":852747,"text":"So we're now able to do very sophisticated\nmotor planning, things like that."},{"time":856352,"text":"I don't have time to explain,\nbut to understand how a brain works,"},{"time":859502,"text":"you have to understand how the first part\nof the mammalian neocortex works,"},{"time":863063,"text":"how it is we store patterns\nand make predictions."},{"time":865380,"text":"Let me give you\na few examples of predictions."},{"time":867592,"text":"I already said the word \"sentence.\""},{"time":869292,"text":"In music, if you've heard a song before,"},{"time":872522,"text":"when you hear it, the next note\npops into your head already --"},{"time":875455,"text":"you anticipate it."},{"time":876630,"text":"With an album, at the end of a song,\nthe next song pops into your head."},{"time":880008,"text":"It happens all the time,\nyou make predictions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":882337,"text":"I have this thing called\nthe \"altered door\" thought experiment."},{"time":885400,"text":"It says, you have a door at home;"},{"time":888253,"text":"when you're here, I'm changing it --"},{"time":890032,"text":"I've got a guy back at your house\nright now, moving the door around,"},{"time":893252,"text":"moving your doorknob over two inches."},{"time":895045,"text":"When you go home tonight, you'll put\nyour hand out, reach for the doorknob,"},{"time":898653,"text":"notice it's in the wrong spot"},{"time":900191,"text":"and go, \"Whoa, something happened.\""},{"time":901902,"text":"It may take a second,\nbut something happened."},{"time":904027,"text":"I can change your doorknob\nin other ways --"},{"time":906054,"text":"make it larger, smaller, change\nits brass to silver, make it a lever,"},{"time":909319,"text":"I can change the door;\nput colors on, put windows in."},{"time":911919,"text":"I can change a thousand things\nabout your door"},{"time":914094,"text":"and in the two seconds\nyou take to open it,"},{"time":916126,"text":"you'll notice something has changed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":917872,"text":"Now, the engineering approach,\nthe AI approach to this,"},{"time":920480,"text":"is to build a door database\nwith all the door attributes."},{"time":923179,"text":"And as you go up to the door,\nwe check them off one at time:"},{"time":926022,"text":"door, door, color ..."},{"time":927392,"text":"We don't do that.\nYour brain doesn't do that."},{"time":929516,"text":"Your brain is making\nconstant predictions all the time"},{"time":932080,"text":"about what will happen\nin your environment."},{"time":934138,"text":"As I put my hand on this table,\nI expect to feel it stop."},{"time":936908,"text":"When I walk, every step,\nif I missed it by an eighth of an inch,"},{"time":939951,"text":"I'll know something has changed."},{"time":941508,"text":"You're constantly making predictions\nabout your environment."},{"time":944352,"text":"I'll talk about vision, briefly."},{"time":945969,"text":"This is a picture of a woman."},{"time":947376,"text":"When we look at people, our eyes saccade\nover two to three times a second."},{"time":950890,"text":"We're not aware of it,\nbut our eyes are always moving."},{"time":953443,"text":"When we look at a face, we typically\ngo from eye to eye to nose to mouth."},{"time":956902,"text":"When your eye moves from eye to eye,"},{"time":958795,"text":"if there was something\nelse there like a nose,"},{"time":960977,"text":"you'd see a nose where an eye\nis supposed to be and go, \"Oh, shit!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":964547,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":965967,"text":"\"There's something wrong\nabout this person.\""},{"time":968100,"text":"That's because you're making a prediction."},{"time":970129,"text":"It's not like you just look over and say,\n\"What am I seeing? A nose? OK.\""},{"time":973592,"text":"No, you have an expectation\nof what you're going to see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":976250,"text":"Every single moment."},{"time":977425,"text":"And finally, let's think\nabout how we test intelligence."},{"time":980078,"text":"We test it by prediction:\nWhat is the next word in this ...?"},{"time":983183,"text":"This is to this as this is to this.\nWhat is the next number in this sentence?"},{"time":986834,"text":"Here's three visions of an object.\nWhat's the fourth one?"},{"time":989548,"text":"That's how we test it.\nIt's all about prediction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":992573,"text":"So what is the recipe for brain theory?"},{"time":995219,"text":"First of all, we have to have\nthe right framework."},{"time":997609,"text":"And the framework is a memory framework,"},{"time":999546,"text":"not a computational or behavior framework,"},{"time":1001594,"text":"it's a memory framework."},{"time":1002781,"text":"How do you store and recall\nthese sequences of patterns?"},{"time":1005428,"text":"It's spatiotemporal patterns."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1006894,"text":"Then, if in that framework,\nyou take a bunch of theoreticians --"},{"time":1009927,"text":"biologists generally\nare not good theoreticians."},{"time":1012197,"text":"Not always, but generally, there's not\na good history of theory in biology."},{"time":1015750,"text":"I've found the best people\nto work with are physicists,"},{"time":1018348,"text":"engineers and mathematicians,"},{"time":1019755,"text":"who tend to think algorithmically."},{"time":1021475,"text":"Then they have to learn\nthe anatomy and the physiology."},{"time":1024763,"text":"You have to make these theories\nvery realistic in anatomical terms."},{"time":1029283,"text":"Anyone who tells you their theory\nabout how the brain works"},{"time":1032072,"text":"and doesn't tell you exactly\nhow it's working"},{"time":1034193,"text":"and how the wiring works --"},{"time":1035520,"text":"it's not a theory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1036811,"text":"And that's what we do\nat the Redwood Neuroscience Institute."},{"time":1039668,"text":"I'd love to tell you we're making\nfantastic progress in this thing,"},{"time":1043000,"text":"and I expect to be back on this stage\nsometime in the not too distant future,"},{"time":1046686,"text":"to tell you about it."},{"time":1047874,"text":"I'm really excited;\nthis is not going to take 50 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1050492,"text":"What will brain theory look like?"},{"time":1052094,"text":"First of all, it's going\nto be about memory."},{"time":1054173,"text":"Not like computer memory --\nnot at all like computer memory."},{"time":1057019,"text":"It's very different."},{"time":1058194,"text":"It's a memory of very\nhigh-dimensional patterns,"},{"time":1060475,"text":"like the things that come from your eyes."},{"time":1062461,"text":"It's also memory of sequences:"},{"time":1063922,"text":"you cannot learn or recall anything\noutside of a sequence."},{"time":1066676,"text":"A song must be heard\nin sequence over time,"},{"time":1069537,"text":"and you must play it back\nin sequence over time."},{"time":1071912,"text":"And these sequences\nare auto-associatively recalled,"},{"time":1074385,"text":"so if I see something, I hear something,\nit reminds me of it,"},{"time":1077282,"text":"and it plays back automatically."},{"time":1078839,"text":"It's an automatic playback."},{"time":1080157,"text":"And prediction of future inputs\nis the desired output."},{"time":1082729,"text":"And as I said, the theory\nmust be biologically accurate,"},{"time":1085373,"text":"it must be testable\nand you must be able to build it."},{"time":1087881,"text":"If you don't build it,\nyou don't understand it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1090116,"text":"One more slide."},{"time":1091672,"text":"What is this going to result in?"},{"time":1094005,"text":"Are we going to really build\nintelligent machines?"},{"time":1096377,"text":"Absolutely. And it's going to be\ndifferent than people think."},{"time":1100508,"text":"No doubt that it's going\nto happen, in my mind."},{"time":1102924,"text":"First of all, we're going to build\nthis stuff out of silicon."},{"time":1106064,"text":"The same techniques we use to build\nsilicon computer memories,"},{"time":1109000,"text":"we can use here."},{"time":1110175,"text":"But they're very different\ntypes of memories."},{"time":1112308,"text":"And we'll attach\nthese memories to sensors,"},{"time":1114355,"text":"and the sensors will experience\nreal-live, real-world data,"},{"time":1117156,"text":"and learn about their environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1118932,"text":"Now, it's very unlikely the first things\nyou'll see are like robots."},{"time":1122401,"text":"Not that robots aren't useful;\npeople can build robots."},{"time":1125000,"text":"But the robotics part is the hardest part.\nThat's old brain. That's really hard."},{"time":1128791,"text":"The new brain is easier\nthan the old brain."},{"time":1130822,"text":"So first we'll do things\nthat don't require a lot of robotics."},{"time":1133928,"text":"So you're not going to see C-3PO."},{"time":1136131,"text":"You're going to see things\nmore like intelligent cars"},{"time":1138640,"text":"that really understand\nwhat traffic is, what driving is"},{"time":1141472,"text":"and have learned that cars\nwith the blinkers on for half a minute"},{"time":1144774,"text":"probably aren't going to turn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1146372,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1147687,"text":"We can also do intelligent\nsecurity systems."},{"time":1149775,"text":"Anytime we're basically using our brain\nbut not doing a lot of mechanics --"},{"time":1153372,"text":"those are the things\nthat will happen first."},{"time":1155455,"text":"But ultimately, the world's the limit."},{"time":1157299,"text":"I don't know how this will turn out."},{"time":1159055,"text":"I know a lot of people who invented\nthe microprocessor."},{"time":1161670,"text":"And if you talk to them,"},{"time":1163858,"text":"they knew what they were doing\nwas really significant,"},{"time":1166457,"text":"but they didn't really know\nwhat was going to happen."},{"time":1168981,"text":"They couldn't anticipate\ncell phones and the Internet"},{"time":1171773,"text":"and all this kind of stuff."},{"time":1173532,"text":"They just knew like,\n\"We're going to build calculators"},{"time":1176177,"text":"and traffic-light controllers."},{"time":1177641,"text":"But it's going to be big!\""},{"time":1178964,"text":"In the same way, brain science\nand these memories"},{"time":1181329,"text":"are going to be a very\nfundamental technology,"},{"time":1183578,"text":"and it will lead to unbelievable changes\nin the next 100 years."},{"time":1187044,"text":"And I'm most excited about\nhow we're going to use them in science."},{"time":1190473,"text":"So I think that's all my time -- I'm over,"},{"time":1193334,"text":"and I'm going to end my talk right there."}]}]}